                     <p> 
                        <pb n="13"/>
                        <placeName key="place_107049">MORTON (South)</placeName>. The <orgName key="org_107004">prior and convent of Wallingford</orgName>
                  declare that they have had peaceable possession of the tithe of a mill of the 
                  <persName>lady <forename>Margaret</forename> de <surname>Saundervill</surname>
                        </persName> in 
                  <placeName key="place_107049">South Morton</placeName>, and that a certain annual rent of 8d. is
                  owing of which they possess no sufficient evidences, the prior and convent
                  quit-claim to the lady Margaret the said rent of 8d. and the tithe of the said mill.
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_107073">Wallingford</placeName> in the feast of the Invention of the Cross, <origDate notBefore="1381-06-22" notAfter="1382-06-21">5 Ric. II</origDate>. 
                  </p>
